[thinking] I need to make sure to add tests after the runtime inheritance. It makes sense to place nested classes close to what they're related to. I’m thinking about whether the Java spec mandates cloning annotation arrays on each call. It does, but `getAnnotationsByType` returns a new array, while the annotation proxy remains the same. Also, `declaredRoles.value()` returns a clone. However, `Resources.value()` shows that mutating the local array doesn't affect the annotation member later. Let's go ahead and edit it!
